+   makes the card its own scroll container and pins a `position: sticky` <th>
+   to the card (which scrolls away) instead of the page. So we give the table
+   its own bounded scroll region — the header pins to the top of THIS wrapper
+   while the rows scroll under it. The wrapper carries the border + rounded
+   corners; the inner table drops its own (and must use `overflow: visible` so
+   the global `table { overflow: hidden }` can't clip the sticky <th>). */
